The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 Chennai, April 5: Non-banking finance company Cholamandalam DBS Finance today said its board had approved a preferential offer to IFC, the investment arm of the World Bank, for around Rs 100 crore. Funds raised from the deal will be used to meet the growth and capital adequacy requirements of Chola DBS. The company will issue 1,08,93,852 fresh shares at Rs 92 apiece.                             
	 New Delhi, April 5: Indirect tax mop-up is likely to be around Rs 2.57 lakh crore for 2009-10, higher than the revised estimate of Rs 2.44 lakh crore. Sources in the finance ministry said collections from customs stood at over Rs 1 lakh crore against the revised estimate of Rs 84,477 crore for the past fiscal.                            
	 Mumbai, April 5: With a view to improve transparency and corporate governance, market regulator Sebi has made it mandatory for all listed companies to disclose their financial results within 45 days of the end of every quarter.                             
	 Mumbai, April 5: The rupee today rose to a 19-month high of 44.45 against the dollar after gaining 45 paise on sustained capital inflows. At the Interbank Foreign Exchange market, the rupee resumed higher at 44.78 per dollar against last weekends 44.90 per dollar.                             
	 New Delhi, April 5: The government today held a mock auction for 3G spectrum and has convened a meeting tomorrow in which the bidders would be informed about the details of the real auction on Friday.                             
	 New Delhi, April 5: Healthcare equipment maker Opto Circuits (India) Ltd has acquired Calcutta-based NS Remedies Ltd for $1.50 million in an all-cash deal.                            
	 New Delhi, April 5: Bharat Sanchar Nigam Limiteds employees union today threatened to go on an indefinite hunger strike from April 12 unless orders were given for wage revision and payment of arrears.
                                                                                                                          
